  "text": "Although cystic fibrosis (CF) is fundamentally a genetic disorder, the majority of patients with CF may ultimately succumb to respiratory failure subsequent to chronic bacterial infections [CITATION_1] . In early childhood, lungs of CF patients are often infected with Staphylococcus aureus and Haemophilus influenzae, but these organisms are usually outnumbered by Pseudomonas aeruginosa as patients become older. However, S. aureus often persists in the airways of CF patients and the role of S.",
